OL,6,FShe added: "In these circumstances and
OL,7,Fafter consultation with police and
OL,8,FCPS, it is no longer appropriate to
OL,9,Fcontinue these proceedings and
OL,10,Ftherefore we are instructed to offer
OL,11,Fno evidence."
OL,13,FThe Court of Appeal in London
OL,14,Fpreviously heard that the prosecution
OL,15,Fcase had heavily featured the evidence
OL,16,Fof the witness, who can only be
OL,17,Freferred to as "Z", claiming he heard
OL,18,Fan alleged "confession" from Robert
OL,19,FFirkins while detained.
