OL,6,F"Devon and Cornwall Police accepts the
OL,7,FCPS has conducted a careful review of
OL,8,Favailable evidence in the case and
OL,9,Fhave concluded that there is no longer
OL,10,Fa realistic prospect of conviction.
OL,11,FConsequently, the CPS has decided not
OL,12,Fto present any evidence before the
OL,13,Fcourt.
OL,15,F"Steps are already underway to manage
OL,16,Fthe acquittal process including the
OL,17,Frelease of Robert Firkins from prison.
OL,18,FLee Firkins will remain in custody due
OL,19,Fto other sentences he is currently
OL,20,Fserving.
