OL,6,FJames Wood KC and Sarah Elliott KC
OL,7,Fwere both part of the original defence
OL,8,Fteams representing the two brothers
OL,9,Faccused of the Fishers' murders.
OL,11,FThey said the case had been dependent
OL,12,Fon alleged "cell confession" evidence
OL,13,Fprovided by a prisoner witness.
OL,15,FJames and Sarah commented: "From the
OL,16,Fmoment of these convictions, we knew
OL,17,Fthe case was a gross miscarriage of
OL,18,Fjustice. Based on an alleged cell
OL,19,Fconfession, it illustrated the
OL,20,Finherent dangers of this kind of
OL,21,Fevidence.
